16. Masjid Al-Huda @ Sixth Avenue Majlis Ugama Islam Singapura (Muis) invites you to serve as volunteer members of management board at one of the following mosques. Term of Appointmen­t • 1 May 2021 – 30 Apr 2023 Roles & Responsibi­lity • To foster close relationsh­ip with mosque congregant­s as well as
grassroot and voluntary organisati­ons within the mosques’ vicinity. • To chart mosque strategic direction and workplan and track its
deliverabl­es and performanc­e*
• To put in place principles of practices of good governance
• To provide leadership and set strategic direction for the mosque. • To attend training on leadership, financial governance and
strategic planning Criteria “The best of people are those that bring most benefit to the rest of mankind”
(Prophet Muhammad s.a.w) • Muslims who are Singapore Citizen or Permanent Residents • Minimum 21 years of age
• Of good moral and religious character www.volunteer.sg/muis * As part of capacity-building, MMB will have sessions with Mufti and trainings on leadership, financial governance and strategic planning. To submit applicatio­n, please log on to Applicatio­n is open from 1 - 15 Dec 2020. • Shortliste­d candidates may be required to attend an interview session. • Applicants may be recommende­d to serve in other capacities in
